    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "it's protection from modification of snapshots after index build, also by-design nodes in network must have different indices (with different crypto-seed) to protect against unbalance-index attack.\r\nBut, if you know that backup was valid, it's ok to do something like:\r\n`touch -d \"2024-01-01T00:00:00\" <datadir>/snapshots/*.idx`\r\n\r\nit's not very user-friendly and likely we will change it in the future, but not very soon due to priorities. \r\n\r\n\r\n",
